==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thermophilic
<hw>Ther`mo*phil"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Thermo-</ets> + Gr. <?/ loving + <ets>-ic</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Heat-loving; -- applied especially to microorganisms such as
certain bacteria, fungi and algae, which grow best at temperatures above
40⟦deg⟧ C (e.g. between 50⟦deg⟧ and 60⟦deg⟧), and in some cases at
temperatures that would kill ordinary microorganisms. They are found in
naturally hot locations, such as at hot springs or the thermal vents at
the ocean bottom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thermophone</ent>⟦br⟧
